Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
set_vt_skew_derate(25.10)                            set_vt_skew_derate(25.10)

Name
       set_vt_skew_derate  -  Assigns fast and slow derate factors to specific
       threshold voltage groups

Syntax
       set_vt_skew_derate

        [-help]

       [-delay_corner <string>]

        [-fast <float>]

        [-hold]

        [-mean]

       [-resetViewListVTSkew]

        [-setup]

        [-sigma]

        [-slow <float>]

       [-threshold_voltage_group <group name>]

        [-viewListVTSkew <string>]

       Assigns fast and slow derate  factors  to  specific  threshold  voltage
       groups.

Parameters
       -help  Prints out the command usage.

       -delay_corner <<string>>
              Specifies the list of delay corners.

       -fast <<float>>
              Specifies  the  derate  factor  to  use when evaluating both the
              early and late paths for a speed-up due to Vth skew shift.

              This derate value is expected to be less than 1.0.

       -hold  Specifies that the derate is applied to the hold component.

       -mean  Specifies that the derate is applied to the mean component.

              The specified derate only applies to mean delays in SOCV  analy-
              sis. If the -mean or -sigma parameter is not specified, the der-
              ate applies to both the delay components.

       -resetViewListVTSkew
              Allows the VT skew view list to be reset.

       -setup Specifies that the derate is applied to the setup component.

       -sigma Specifies that the derate is applied to the sigma component.

              The  specified derate only applies to the delay variation compo-
              nent  in SOCV analysis.

       -slow <<float>>
              Specifies the derate factor to  use  when  evaluating  both  the
              early and late paths for a slow-down due to Vth skew shift.

              This derate value is expected to be greater than 1.0.

       -threshold_voltage_group <<group name>>
              Specifies  the threshold voltage group that is either predefined
              in Liberty or defined using the set_voltage_threshold_group com-
              mand.

       -viewListVTSkew <<string>>
              Specifies the VT skew view list.

Examples
              * The following commands define the VT skew derate factors,  and
                customize  the  different  path combinations to be analyzed in
                PBA mode:

                set_vt_skew_derate -threshold_voltage_group  SVT   -fast  0.90
                -slow 1.10

                set_vt_skew_derate  -threshold_voltage_group  LVT   -fast 0.91
                -slow 1.11

                set_vt_skew_derate -threshold_voltage_group  ULVT  -fast  0.92
                -slow 1.12

                set_vt_skew_derate  -threshold_voltage_group  ELVT  -fast 0.93
                -slow 1.13

